[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{With 6 points, SOUTH must respond to NORTH's 1\C opening bid. 
While it is often correct to respond by bidding suits "up-the-line", SOUTH should 
skip over the weak \D suit in favor of showing the 4-card 
Major \S suit.

NORTH knows that SOUTH may only have four \Ss, but with four of her own she can support the 
suit. Since she has a minimum opening bid she merely raises to 2\S. 
With his minimum response hand SOUTH passes.}

